Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil over high heat. When boiling, stir in and dissolve the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Stir in the @pearl barley{75%g}. Bring back to the boil then reduce the heat slightly and cook until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and return to the pan. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm until everything else is ready.

In the meantime, drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a sieve. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop them in half. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Zest and quarter the @lemon{1}.

Lightly oil two #baking trays{}. Pop the @diced sweet potato{200%g} and chickpeas onto one and drizzle on another splash of oil. Sprinkle over the @ground cumin{2%tsp}, @harissa spice mix{1} and a pinch of @salt{}. Toss to combine. Pop the aubergine and tomatoes onto the other #baking tray{} then season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Drizzle over some oil.

Place both trays in the oven, the chickpeas on the middle shelf and the veggies on the top. Cook until the chickpeas are crunchy and the veggies are tender and coloured, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

When everything is ready, gently mix all the roasted veggies and the chickpeas through the drained pearl barley. Mix in the lemon zest, coriander and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop the @wild rocket{40%g} into a large #bowl{} and squeeze over a little lemon juice, toss to combine. Share the jumble between your plates and crumble over the @feta cheese{75%g}. Serve the rocket alongside. Enjoy!

> Use less harissa spice mix if you're not a fan of heat.

> Rocket is a good source of calcium - a perfect addition to this dish.